==English==

===Pronunciation===
'''Pe*lo-ponn*ese'''
PEH-loh-pah-neez

===Etymology===
[[Pelops]], a Greek mythical legend.

===Proper noun===
'''Peloponnese'''
# Also [[Peloponnesus]].  A region in west-central Greece.  It contains [[Achaea]], [[Arcadia]], [[Argolis]], [[Corinthia]], [[Elia]], [[Laconia]] and [[Messenia]].  Known as [[Morea]] in medieval times.

